The desire for spice is part of what drove European seafaring
and contact with the Americas. In fact, the Dutch were so hungry
for nutmeg that in late 1600s that they traded their colony of
New Amsterdam to Britain in exchange for Pulau Run, a
nutmeg-producing Banda Island over which Britain claimed
control. The British renamed the colony “New York.” Today,
